org.beryx.streamplify

Interface Streamable<T,S extends Streamable<T,S>>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BigIntegerCartesianProduct, BigIntegerCombinations, BigIntegerDerangements, BigIntegerIndexedSpliterator, BigIntegerPartialPermutations, BigIntegerPermutations, BigIntegerPowerSet, CartesianProduct, Combinations, Derangements, LongCartesianProduct, LongCombinations, LongDerangements, LongIndexedSpliterator, LongPartialPermutations, LongPermutations, LongPowerSet, PartialPermutations, Permutations, PowerSet, StreamableProxy

    public interface Streamable<T,S extends Streamable<T,S>>
    Objects implementing this interface provide data in form of sequential or parallel Streams.

      • skip

        <Z extends Streamable<T,?>> Z skip(long n)
        Configure this instance to provide streams that skip the first {}@code n} elements in the data source. It is usually more efficient to call this method instead of Stream.skip(long).
        Parameters:
        n - the number of elements to be skipped (as a long).
        Returns:
        depending on the implementation, it may return this instance or another Streamable.

      • shuffle

        <Z extends Streamable<T,?>> Z shuffle(java.util.Random random)
        Configure this instance to provide streams that shuffle elements in the data source.

      • shuffle

        default <Z extends Streamable<T,?>> Z shuffle()
        Configure this instance to provide streams that shuffle elements in the data source.
        This default implementation calls shuffle(Random) with a random number generator created using the parameterless constructor of Random.
        Returns:
        depending on the implementation, it may return this instance or another Streamable.
